Product Name: MiKare

1. Project Information
MiKare is a secure, AI-powered web and mobile platform that lets users record medical consultations, upload health data, track symptoms, mood and medications, and receive AI-generated insights and suggestions. All data is owned and controlled by the user yet easily shared with providers.

2. Objectives / Goals

Empower users to capture and manage their complete health journey.

Improve health literacy with AI-driven summaries and explanations.

Enhance patient–provider collaboration through data exports and question prompts.

Reduce misdiagnosis by providing a longitudinal, structured record of symptoms, labs, and notes.

3. Assumptions & Constraints

Users have internet access and a modern browser or mobile device.

Supabase supports authentication, storage, RLS and functions integrations.

AI services (Whisper, GPT) are available via API.

Must comply with HIPAA, GDPR, OAIC.

No direct EHR integrations in initial release.

4. Background & Strategic Fit
Patients face fragmented records and memory gaps, leading to delayed or incorrect diagnoses. MiKare gives patients control of their data, fosters trust, and equips both users and clinicians with clearer, richer context. The solution aligns with healthcare’s shift to patient engagement and AI-driven support.

5. Scope: User Stories & Requirements

As a user, I can record and transcribe appointments.

As a user, I can upload and organize lab reports and scans.

As a user, I can track symptoms, mood, and medications over time.

As a user, I can view AI summaries and suggested questions.

As a user, I can export my full health package for a provider.

6. Product Features

Audio recording + AI transcription

Conversation highlights and summaries

Chronological diary of events

Document repository with AI analysis

Symptom, mood, medication trackers

AI-driven insights and question suggestions

Multi-profile (family) support

Secure data export (PDF/JSON)

Time-zone aware entries and user-controlled session timeout

7. Release Criteria

Core flows (record, upload, track, export) end-to-end tested

Usability validated with target users aged 18–80

90%+ transcription accuracy on clear audio

No data leaks or security incidents in QA

Mobile and web UIs responsive and accessible

8. Success Metrics

≥75% of users record at least one appointment within first week

≥60% engage with AI suggestions

≥50% export data to share with provider

Zero critical security vulnerabilities

80%+ task completion rate in usability testing

9. Technology Stack

Frontend: React, React Native, Tailwind CSS, Lucide-React

Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage, Functions)

AI: OpenAI Whisper for transcription, GPT for summarisation

Hosting: Vercel / Expo / Supabase managed cloud

Security: TLS 1.3, AES-256 at rest, RLS policies

10. Exclusions

No direct EHR or hospital system integrations

No offline data entry in MVP

AI does not provide diagnoses or medical advice

No third-party UI libraries beyond Lucide icons and Tailwind